==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paramorph
<hw>Par"a*morph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + Gr. <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A kind of pseudomorph, in which there has been a
change of physical characters, by a change in crystal structure without
alteration of chemical composition, as the change of aragonite to
calcite; called also <altname>allomorph</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A taxonomic variant observed
within a species, for which a more specific term has not been
assigned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>par`a*mor"phic</wf>, <pos>a.</pos> --
<wf>par`a*mor"phous</wf>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paramorphism</ent>⟦br⟧
